00099 static void rna_userdef_show_manipulator_update(Main *bmain, Scene *scene, PointerRNA *ptr)
00100 {
00101     UserDef *userdef = (UserDef *)ptr->data;
00102 
00103     /* lame, loop over all views and set */
00104     bScreen *sc;
00105     ScrArea *sa;
00106     SpaceLink *sl;
00107 
00108     /* from scene copy to the other views */
00109     for (sc = bmain->screen.first; sc; sc = sc->id.next) {
00110         for (sa = sc->areabase.first; sa; sa = sa->next) {
00111             for (sl = sa->spacedata.first; sl; sl = sl->next) {
00112                 if (sl->spacetype == SPACE_VIEW3D) {
00113                     View3D *v3d = (View3D *)sl;
00114                     if (userdef->tw_flag & V3D_USE_MANIPULATOR)
00115                         v3d->twflag |= V3D_USE_MANIPULATOR;
00116                     else
00117                         v3d->twflag &= ~V3D_USE_MANIPULATOR;
00118                 }
00119             }
00120         }
00121     }
00122     
00123     rna_userdef_update(bmain, scene, ptr);

00195 static void rna_userdef_timecode_style_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)
00196 {
00197     UserDef *userdef = (UserDef*)ptr->data;
00198     int required_size = userdef->v2d_min_gridsize;
00199     
00200     /* set the timecode style */
00201     userdef->timecode_style = value;
00202     
00203     /* adjust the v2d gridsize if needed so that timecodes don't overlap
00204      * NOTE: most of these have been hand-picked to avoid overlaps while still keeping
00205      * things from getting too blown out
00206      */
00207     switch (value) {
00208         case USER_TIMECODE_MINIMAL:
00209         case USER_TIMECODE_SECONDS_ONLY:
00210             /* 35 is great most of the time, but not that great for full-blown */
00211             required_size = 35;
00212             break;
00213         case USER_TIMECODE_SMPTE_MSF:
00214             required_size = 50;
00215             break;
00216         case USER_TIMECODE_SMPTE_FULL:
00217             /* the granddaddy! */
00218             required_size = 65;
00219             break;
00220         case USER_TIMECODE_MILLISECONDS:
00221             required_size = 45;
00222             break;
00223     }
00224     
00225     if (U.v2d_min_gridsize < required_size)
00226         U.v2d_min_gridsize = required_size;
00227 }

00362 static EnumPropertyItem *rna_userdef_compute_device_itemf(bContext *UNUSED(C), PointerRNA *UNUSED(ptr),
00363                                                           PropertyRNA *UNUSED(prop), int *free)
00364 {
00365     EnumPropertyItem tmp = {0, "", 0, "", ""};
00366     EnumPropertyItem *item = NULL;
00367     int totitem = 0;
00368     
00369     if (U.compute_device_type == USER_COMPUTE_DEVICE_NONE) {
00370         /* only add a single CPU device */
00371         tmp.value = 0;
00372         tmp.name = "CPU";
00373         tmp.identifier = "CPU";
00374         RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &tmp);
00375     }
00376     else {
00377         /* get device list from cycles. it would be good to make this generic
00378            once we have more subsystems using opencl, for now this is easiest */
00379         int opencl = (U.compute_device_type == USER_COMPUTE_DEVICE_OPENCL);
00380         CCLDeviceInfo *devices = CCL_compute_device_list(opencl);
00381         int a;
00382 
00383         if (devices) {
00384             for (a = 0; devices[a].name; a++) {
00385                 tmp.value = devices[a].value;
00386                 tmp.identifier = devices[a].identifier;
00387                 tmp.name = devices[a].name;
00388                 RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &tmp);
00389             }
00390         }
00391         else {
00392             tmp.value = 0;
00393             tmp.name = "CPU";
00394             tmp.identifier = "CPU";
00395             RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &tmp);
00396         }
00397     }
00398 
00399     RNA_enum_item_end(&item, &totitem);
00400     *free = 1;
00401 
00402     return item;
